CAPE TOWN - Messages of condolences have been pouring in for former Springbok coach and GOOD councilor Peter de Villiers after losing his wife in a tragic incident on Sunday. Theresa de Villiers apparently drowned in a swimming pool while visiting relatives in Gqeberha. GOOD party leader Patricia de Lille was among those who extended their condolences to the bereaved family. The party's Samkelo Mgobozi said, "The GOOD party leader has sent her heartfelt condolences to the de Villiers family following the tragic passing of his beloved wife. May strength, peace, love surround you and your family, Coach, as you go through this difficult time." An inquest docket has been opened. GOOD extends its most heartfelt condolences to @CoachPdV, former SA rugby coach and GOOD Councillor, on the passing of his beloved wife.Our thoughts and prayers go out to you. May strength, peace, love surround you as you and your family go through this difficult time. 